  "text": "Comprehensive audit of Envoy TLS certificate validation files in v1.31.2:\n\n## Server Certificate Validation (Client validates Server)\n\nWhen a client (upstream) connects to a server, the client validates the server's certificate. This is handled through:\n\n1. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc** (lines 315, 481-528, 280-330):\n   - `X509_verify_cert()` - Core OpenSSL function to verify certificate chain\n   - `addClientValidationContext()` - Called by client context to set SSL_CTX_set_verify with SSL_VERIFY_PEER\n   - `doVerifyCertChain()` - Performs actual verification using OpenSSL\n   - Supports certificate hash pinning and SPKI validation\n\n2. **source/common/tls/context_impl.cc** (lines 181, 474, 512-533):\n   - `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify()` - Sets up custom verification callback for async validation\n   - `customVerifyCallback()` - Entry point for certificate verification logic\n   - `customVerifyCertChain()` - Performs async certificate chain validation\n\n3. **source/common/tls/client_context_impl.cc** (line 114):\n   - `SSL_set_verify()` - Configures SSL connection to verify server certificate\n\n4. **source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc** (lines 177, 194-209):\n   - SPIFFE-specific certificate validation using `X509_verify_cert()`\n   - Performs certificate precheck and trust bundle validation\n\n## Client Certificate Validation (Server validates Client)\n\nWhen a server receives a connection, it may validate the client's certificate. This is handled through:\n\n1. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc** (lines 481-530, 543):\n   - `addClientValidationContext()` - Configures server to validate client certs\n   - Uses `SSL_CTX_set_verify(ctx, SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT, nullptr)` when required\n   - `SSL_CTX_set_verify_depth()` - Sets max certificate chain depth\n\n2. **source/common/tls/server_context_impl.cc** (line 147-148):\n   - Calls `cert_validator_->addClientValidationContext()` to set up client certificate validation\n   - Configuration comes from server context config's requireClientCertificate setting\n\n## Core Certificate Validation Infrastructure\n\n1. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/cert_validator.h**:\n   - Abstract interface defining `addClientValidationContext()`, `doVerifyCertChain()`, and `initializeSslContexts()`\n   - Provides validation result structure with status, detailed_status, and error details\n\n2. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.h**:\n   - Concrete implementation of CertValidator interface\n   - Declares methods for certificate verification including SAN matching, hash pinning, and SPKI pinning\n\n3. **source/common/tls/utility.cc** (line 461):\n   - `getX509VerificationErrorInfo()` - Processes X509_verify_cert error information\n   - Uses `X509_verify_cert_error_string()` to get error descriptions\n\n4. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/utility.h/cc**:\n   - Utility functions for certificate expiration handling\n   - `setIgnoreCertificateExpiration()` - Can bypass expiration validation\n\n5. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/san_matcher.h/cc**:\n   - Subject Alternative Name validation for certificate verification\n   - Supports string matching and custom matchers\n\n## TLS Context and Configuration Files\n\n1. **source/common/tls/context_config_impl.h/cc**:\n   - Manages certificate validation context configuration\n   - Handles combined validation context for dynamic certificate loading\n\n2. **source/common/tls/server_context_config_impl.h/cc**:\n   - Server-specific configuration with requireClientCertificate option\n\n3. **source/common/tls/ssl_socket.cc** (lines 114, 216-221):\n   - Tracks certificate validation errors\n   - Processes SSL_R_CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED and SSL_R_PEER_DID_NOT_RETURN_A_CERTIFICATE errors\n\n4. **source/common/tls/ssl_handshaker.cc** (line 38-40):\n   - `setCertificateValidationStatus()` - Sets certificate validation status on extended socket info\n\n5. **source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/upstream_config.h/cc, downstream_config.h/cc**:\n   - Transport socket configuration for upstream (client) and downstream (server) contexts\n   - Instantiates certificate validators based on configuration\n\n## Key Verification Modes Used\n\n- **SSL_VERIFY_PEER** - Verify peer certificate\n- **SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT** - Fail if no peer certificate provided (client validation requirement)\n- **SSL_VERIFY_NONE** - No verification (when validation is disabled)\n\n## Summary\n\nServer certificate validation (client validates server) is handled primarily through DefaultCertValidator's `doVerifyCertChain()` method which calls `X509_verify_cert()`, with async support via `customVerifyCallback()` and `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify()`.\n\nClient certificate validation (server validates client) is configured through `addClientValidationContext()` which sets `SSL_CTX_set_verify()` on the server's SSL context. The server configuration option `requireClientCertificate` controls whether this validation is mandatory.\n\nBoth paths support:\n- Certificate chain validation\n- Subject Alternative Name (SAN) matching\n- Certificate hash pinning (SHA-256)\n- SPKI pinning (Subject Public Key Info)\n- Certificate expiration validation (with optional bypass)\n- Custom validators (SPIFFE)\n- Asynchronous validation via callbacks"
